<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="247" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1356,1598]" pageId="21" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1464,1490]" pageId="21" pageNumber="247">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is by far the most widely distributed of the genus, ranging from 
<collectingCountry box="[1199,1320,1464,1490]" name="Guatemala" pageId="21" pageNumber="247">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Drake, C. J. &amp; Harris, H. M." pageId="21" pageNumber="247" pagination="95 - 97" refId="ref8993" refString="Drake, C. J. &amp; Harris, H. M. (1942) A new Brachymetra from Venezuela (Hemiptera-Gerridae). Boletin de Entomologia Venezolana, 1, 95 - 97." type="journal article" year="1942">Drake &amp; Harris 1942</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<collectingCountry box="[328,432,1500,1526]" name="Paraguay" pageId="21" pageNumber="247">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Drake, C. J. &amp; Harris, H. M." box="[447,689,1500,1526]" pageId="21" pageNumber="247" pagination="235 - 239" refId="ref8918" refString="Drake, C. J. &amp; Harris, H. M. (1930) Notes on some South American Gerridae (Hemiptera). Annals of the Carnegie Museum, 19, 235 - 239." type="journal article" year="1930">Drake &amp; Harris 1930</bibRefCitation>
). It has three previous records from 
<collectingCountry box="[1092,1181,1500,1526]" name="Panama" pageId="21" pageNumber="247">Panama</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Allee, W. C. &amp; Torvik, M." box="[1195,1431,1500,1526]" pageId="21" pageNumber="247" pagination="66 - 71" refId="ref8246" refString="Allee, W. C. &amp; Torvik, M. (1927) Factors Affecting Animal Distribution in a Small Stream of the Panama Rain-Forest in the Dry Season. Journal of Ecology, 15, 66 - 71. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2256064" type="journal article" year="1927">Allee &amp; Torvik 1927</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shaw, J. G." box="[151,278,1536,1562]" pageId="21" pageNumber="247" pagination="221 - 233" refId="ref11264" refString="Shaw, J. G. (1933) A study of the Genus Brachymetra (Hemiptera - Gerridae). University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 21, 221 - 233." type="journal article" year="1933">Shaw 1933</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingRegion box="[341,434,1536,1562]" country="Panama" name="Chiriqui" pageId="21" pageNumber="247">Chiriquí</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Champion, G. C." box="[449,631,1536,1562]" pageId="21" pageNumber="247" refId="ref8522" refString="Champion, G. C. (1898) Insecta. Rhynchota. Hemiptera-Heteroptera. In: Godman, F. D. &amp; Salvin, O. (Eds.), Biologia Centrali- Americana. Vol. II. Taylor &amp; Francis, London, pp. i - xvi + 1 - 416 pp., 22 pls." type="book" year="1898">Champion 1898</bibRefCitation>
) provinces, and the occurrence in 
<collectingRegion box="[1018,1193,1536,1562]" country="Panama" name="Colon" pageId="21" pageNumber="247">Colón Province</collectingRegion>
is herein reported for the first time.
</paragraph>
